      • FsRemoteSend

        public FsRemoteSend​(java.lang.String remote,
                    java.lang.String path,
                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Object> options)
             throws java.lang.Throwable
        Constructor taking a com.qoretechnologies.qorus.DbRemote "DbRemote" object for the remote server
        Parameters:
        remote - a string giving the name of the remoteconn "remote connection" for the remote server
        path - a string with full or relative path of the target file (inluding file name)
        options - optional stream-api-options as follows:
        • "timeout": an HTTP socket timeout value in milliseconds; used locally and in the remote for socket I/O and queue operations; default value: "5m"
        • "loglevel": a default log level option for logging; see LogLevels for valid value
        • "block": data block size (default 16384, minimum 4096); the number of bytes sent in each datastreamprotocol "DataStream" protocol chunk
        • "queue_block_size": the number of blocks to queue for sending before the main data thread will block (default: 2)
        • "queue_timeout": the number of milliseconds to wait for queue data before throwing a "QUEUE-TIMEOUT" exception
        • "no_remote_timeout": if True the "timeout" option will not be sent to the remote
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        Note:
        • to calculate the total data queued for the socket I/O thread, multiply block by queue_block_size (default 16384 * 2 = 32768 bytes)
        • the explicit or default timeout value here overrides any socket I/O timeout set for the remote connection object

    • Method Detail

      • commit

        public void commit()
            throws java.lang.Throwable
        This method flushes all buffered I/O to the remote server and returns when all data have been sent to the server and the socket I/O thread has terminated Example: 
        
FsRemoteSend fs = new FsRemoteSend(qrest, target_path, opts);
try {
    // send all strings in an array of strings
    for (String str : array) {
        fs.append(str);
    }
    // finalize the data transfer
    fs.commit();
} catch (Throwable e) {
    // cancel the send stream
    fs.cancel();
} finally {
    // release the weak reference to the Qore object
    fs.release();
}
        Log messages are created with performance information (bytes send, time of transfer, bytes / second, etc).
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        See Also:
        flush()
        Note:
        • either this method, flush() or cancel() should be called to ensure that all data has been sent
        • exceptions thrown in the socket I/O thread will be rethrown when this method is called so that errors can be handled in the main data thread
        • equivalent to flush()

      • cancel

        public void cancel()
            throws java.lang.Throwable
        This method purges any queued I/O and stops the socket thread and returns when the socket I/O thread has terminated Example: 
        
FsRemoteSend fs = new FsRemoteSend(qrest, target_path, opts);
try {
    // send all strings in an array of strings
    for (String str : array) {
        fs.append(str);
    }
    // finalize the data transfer
    fs.commit();
} catch (Throwable e) {
    // cancel the send stream
    fs.cancel();
} finally {
    // release the weak reference to the Qore object
    fs.release();
}
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        Note:
        either this method or commit() should be called to ensure that all data has been sent

      • append

        public void append​(java.lang.String data)
            throws java.lang.Throwable
        Append data to the ready queue Example: 
        
FsRemoteSend fs = new FsRemoteSend(qrest, target_path, opts);
try {
    // send all strings in an array of strings
    for (String str : array) {
        fs.append(str);
    }
    // finalize the data transfer
    fs.commit();
} catch (Throwable e) {
    // cancel the send stream
    fs.cancel();
} finally {
    // release the weak reference to the Qore object
    fs.release();
}
        Data are queued for sending when the buffered byte count reaches the "block" size.
        Parameters:
        data - data to be sent
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        Note:
        • make sure to call either commit() (to flush all data to the server) or cancel() (to cancel the I/O operation) before continuing (see the example above)
        • exceptions thrown in the socket I/O thread will be rethrown when this method is called so that errors can be handled in the main data thread

      • rename

        public void rename​(java.lang.String target,
                   boolean man)
            throws java.lang.Throwable
        Executes an implicit commit() and renames/moves the file given in "path" in the constructor() Example: 
        
FsRemoteSend fs = new FsRemoteSend(qrest, target_path, opts);
try {
    // send all strings in an array of strings
    for (String str : array) {
        fs.append(str);
    }
    // finalize the data transfer
    fs.commit();
    // rename the file after the transfer
    fs.rename(final_name);
} catch (Throwable e) {
    // cancel the send stream
    fs.cancel();
} finally {
    // release the weak reference to the Qore object
    fs.release();
}
        Parameters:
        target - a new path with filename. Relative to user connection if the user connection constructor is used.
        man - rename the file manually by copying the file's data and then deleting the source file, this is sometimes necessary on some OSes when renaming files across filesystem boundaries
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        Note:
        do not call this method before all data have been sent (ie call only after calling commit() first as in the example above)
        Warning:
        The original file after the rename does not exist anymore if "man" is set to True. Any additional append() call will result in an exception.

      • del

        public void del()
         throws java.lang.Throwable
        Executes an implicit commit() and deletes the file given in "path" in the constructor() Example:

try {

    fs.commit();

    fs.del();
} catch (Throwable e) {
    // cancel the send stream
    fs.cancel();
} finally {
    // release the weak reference to the Qore object
    fs.release();
}
